title.narrative: WASH NORTH SYRIA

description.narrative: Syria's conflict-affected population have their critical Water, Sanitation, and Hygiene (WASH) needs met, in line with the HRP and as part of the UNICEF JOP, which contributes to Other Cross-Sectoral Programme Areas, Sanitation, Sanitation (Covid), Water, Water (Covid). UNICEF aims to achieve this through Systems Strengthening And Institution Building. This contributes to the following Country Programme result: MENARO delivers timely, equitable and principled humanitarian action as a complement to country office-led operations where required, including through the cross-border component of the Syria programmes as part of the Whole of Syria response.

title.narrative: Syria's conflict-affected population have their critical WASH needs met, in line with the HRP and as part of the UNICEF JOP

description.narrative: During 2021, 1,557,870 people, including 819,338 children, benefitted from WASH services and supplies. WASH programme enhanced focus on resilience with increased emphasis on rehabilitation of WASH services benefiting 832,285 residents, apart from addressing critical emergency needs for 725,585 internally displaced people. Emphasis on COVID19 preventive measures continued, by expanding the scope of hygiene promotion, with promotion of social distancing and use of masks. Strategic partnership with UNHCR and WFP helped outreaching most vulnerable people and enhanced;quality of response. Collaboration with INGOs helped shifting the responsibility for 136,000 displaced people, intending to reduce adverse impact of UNSCR potential non-renewal. | Status:Met | As-of Date:01/02/2022
